This is a simple http server (only GET without parameters).

Usage:
  http_serv [-i ip] [-p port] [-r dir] [-l log] [-d daemon mode] [-h help]

-i - ip of http server, mandatory parameter.
-p - listen port of http server, mandatory parameter.
-r - root directory. The absolute path to working directory of a http server. Mandatory parametr. 
-l - log file, optional parametr.
-d - daemon mode, optional parametr.
-h - help

Example:
  http_serv -i 127.0.0.1 -p 8181 -r /path/to/http/root -d
